  "target_response": {
    "text": "Worth knowing up front: with manual logging there's no sensor computing a recovery score, so the 67 target can't actually be measured yet — that's the first thing to fix if the number matters to you, since a wrist or ring tracker would populate it. But the behaviors that raise recovery scores don't wait for a gadget. Start with sleep, your biggest lever: last night you logged 7.0 h, a decent base to build consistency on — same bedtime nightly, including weekends. Second, space your hard training days so consecutive heavy sessions are rare. Third, log workouts and a quick morning energy rating daily; that gives us a trend to coach against even without a score. Do those for a few weeks and the score, once you can see it, will likely already be moving.",
